          "badge": "Nursing Mocks",
          "subtitle": "<p>Preparing for the TEAS 7 can feel a little chaotic at first — almost like\ntrying to study with ten different tabs open in your brain. You’re reviewing\nscience facts one minute, then diving into reading passages the next, wondering\nhow on earth you’re supposed to keep all of this straight. The truth is, every\nTEAS section has its own personality. Once you learn what each part is really\nchecking for, your study routine starts to feel more intentional and far less\noverwhelming.<o:p></o:p></p>\n\n<p data-start=\"863\" data-end=\"1190\">This guide breaks each section down in a\nsimple, practical way — the same way nursing students talk about the test when\nthey swap study tips during late-night group sessions. If you take your time,\npay attention to the small patterns, and stay consistent, you’ll walk into your\nTEAS exam with more confidence than you expected.<o:p></o:p></p>",
          "title": "Best Way for Students to Study for ATI TEAS 7",
